- VSCode Version: 1.0.0
- OS Version: OS X Yosemite
- Language: TypeScript

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Paste the following code snippet into VS Code

```
export class Test {
    private static _meta = {
        foo: "string"
    };

    private p = Test._meta;

    private static test(me: Test) {
        var myTestVar = me.p.foo;
    }
}
```
1. Right click on foo on line 3 and select rename symbol
2. Change "foo" to "fooNew" and press enter
3. Expected: me.p.foo should be updated to me.p.fooNew
4. Actual: rename does not work leaving broken code that does not build

It may be worth mentioning that this code snippet is just a trivial example to highlight the problem. So in case you are wondering why anyone would want to do this, we do have a valid use case that's just too complex to put here. Also, Visual Studio handles the refactoring just fine.

